1. Create an IAM user for doing the task
2. Create CLI keys for the user
3. Download the code.js
4. run code
    i. npm install
    ii. node index.js
5. Dockerize app
6. Download docker and install
    For building the image:
        # docker build -t tiny_app:v1
    For running the container:
        # docker run -d -p 80:3000 mahiketh/tiny_app:v1
7. Create an AWS ec2 instance with amazon linux 2023
8. Create Security Group
    i. Inbound rule - Allow ssh port 22 on my_ip
                        Allow http port 80 from Anywhere (All IPs)
    ii. Outbound rule - Allow all traffic from Anywhere
9. Attach SG to the ec2
10. aws configure- Give cli keys
11. Create a bucket
    aws s3api create-bucket --bucket particle41-dev-state-files --region us-east-1
    aws s3api put-bucket-versioning --bucket particle41-dev-state-files --versioning-configuration Status=Enabled
    aws s3api put-bucket-encryption --bucket particle41-dev-state-files --server-side-encryption-configuration '{"Rules":[{"ApplyServerSideEncryptionByDefault":{"SSEAlgorithm":"AES256"}}]}'

12. Create a vpc module
13. Create VPC using teraform
14. Create SG